<section class="hero" style="min-height:auto;padding:8rem 2rem 3rem">
<h1>PRIVACY POLICIES</h1>
<p class="subtitle">PER-PRODUCT DATA HANDLING</p>
<p class="tagline">Each product has different data requirements. Each gets its own policy. No blanket statements — just honest, specific disclosures.</p>
</section>
<section>
<div class="privacy-grid">
<a href="privacy-crypt.html" class="privacy-card">
<span class="badge" style="border-color:#4da6ff;color:#4da6ff">ANDROID</span>
<h3 style="color:#4da6ff">AMNI-CRYPT</h3>
<p>File encryption. All cryptographic operations local. No accounts. Free tier ad-supported (AdMob collects device/ad data per Google's policy). Premium removes ads entirely.</p>
</a>
<a href="privacy-haven.html" class="privacy-card">
<span class="badge" style="border-color:#7c5cfc;color:#7c5cfc">ANDROID</span>
<h3 style="color:#7c5cfc">AMNI-HAVEN</h3>
<p>Mobile client for ANCSemi's Haven servers. Data transmitted to your chosen server. Free tier ad-supported (AdMob). FCM for push notifications. Server-side data governed by your operator.</p>
</a>
<a href="privacy-ai.html" class="privacy-card">
<span class="badge" style="border-color:#ffb74d;color:#ffb74d">DESKTOP</span>
<h3 style="color:#ffb74d">AMNI-AI</h3>
<p>Local intelligence engine. Fully offline. No accounts, no cloud, no telemetry. Everything runs on your hardware.</p>
</a>
<a href="privacy-core.html" class="privacy-card">
<span class="badge" style="border-color:#ef5350;color:#ef5350">PLATFORM</span>
<h3 style="color:#ef5350">AMNI-CORE</h3>
<p>Systems platform. No telemetry, no data collection, no phone-home. Operates entirely on local hardware.</p>
</a>
</div>
</section>
<section>
<h2>GENERAL PRINCIPLES</h2>
<div class="features">
<div class="feature">
<div class="icon">&#128270;</div>
<h4>TRANSPARENT</h4>
<p>Every product discloses exactly what data it handles, what third parties are involved, and what permissions it needs.</p>
</div>
<div class="feature">
<div class="icon">&#128274;</div>
<h4>MINIMAL COLLECTION</h4>
<p>Products that can operate offline do. Products that need network access disclose what goes where and why.</p>
</div>
<div class="feature">
<div class="icon">&#128203;</div>
<h4>NO BLANKET CLAIMS</h4>
<p>Different products have different requirements. We won't pretend a chat client and an encryption tool handle data the same way.</p>
</div>
</div>
</section>
